# Implementation Plan: Academic Humanizer Visual Dashboard

This plan outlines the development of a professional-grade web UI for the Academic Humanizer. This UI will eliminate the need to edit Python files and provide real-time visual feedback on the humanization process.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Hosting Clarification:** GitHub Pages only hosts **static** websites (HTML/CSS). Since your agent requires a Python backend to run LangGraph and call the Groq API, it **cannot** be hosted on GitHub Pages for free. 
> 
> **Alternative:** I will build this as a **Local Web App** using **Streamlit**. You will run it with one command, and it will open a beautiful interface in your browser that looks and feels like a professional website.

## Proposed Changes

### [New Project Components]

#### [NEW] [humanizer_app.py](file:///c:/YERBO/Desktop/cover%20leter/CL/humanizer_app.py)
A new Streamlit-based application that acts as the visual frontend. Key features include:
- **File Uploader:** Drag-and-drop support for `.pdf` and `.docx` files.
- **Entity Dashboard:** Shows which technical terms were "Locked" by the agent.
- **Metric Visualizer:** A real-time chart showing the Burstiness score increasing across iterations.
- **Live Logs:** A visual feed showing the "Agent's Thoughts" as it works.

#### [MODIFY] [humanizer_agent.py](file:///c:/YERBO/Desktop/cover%20leter/CL/humanizer_agent.py)
Small refactoring to make the LangGraph app importable into the UI without running the `if __name__ == "__main__"` test code.

### [Phase 1: File Parsing Engine]
Implemented inside the UI to handle:
- **PDF Extraction:** Using `PyMuPDF`.
- **Word Extraction:** Using `python-docx`.
- Splitting large documents into manageable chunks for the LLM.

### [Phase 2: Premium UI Design]
- **Sidebar:** For API settings and Iteration Limit controls.
- **Main Area:** Split-screen view (Original Text vs. Humanized Result).
- **Theme:** Dark mode by default for a premium, developer-centric feel.

### [Phase 3: Integration]
Connecting the "Apply Humanization" button in the UI to the LangGraph execution loop.

## Open Questions

- **Chunking Logic:** If you upload a 50-page PDF, the LLM cannot process it all at once. Should the UI process it **page-by-page** or **paragraph-by-paragraph**?
- **Download Format:** Would you like the final humanized output to be downloadable as a new Word document or simply copied as text?

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Validate PDF text extraction against a sample research paper.
- Test UI responsiveness during the LangGraph loop.

### Manual Verification
- Verify that clicking "Humanize" updates the visual charts and live logs.
- Test the "Download" functionality for Word files.
